<SLUG> BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo, 2nd Ld-Writethru,0882 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
U.S. bombers prepare for airstrikes amid marathon Kosovo talks
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: LEADS to UPDATE with Holbrooke comments &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos BEL101,PRI101-104,XAVI102,LON103 &QL; 
 &UR; By VESELIN TOSHKOV &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) _ With NATO gearing up for airstrikes,
U.S. envoy Richard Holbrooke and Yugoslavia's president met Sunday
for 11 hours of ``intense'' and ``at times very heated'' talks in a
final push to solve the Kosovo crisis through diplomacy.
