w2738 &Cx1f; wstm-
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Sports-IceHockey-NHLR     10-12 0244
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Ice Hockey-NHL Roundup,0243 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Flyers 4, Mighty Ducks 1
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PHILADELPHIA (AP) _ Eric Lindros scored his first two goals of
the season as the Philadelphia Flyers beat the Anaheim Mighty Ducks
4-1 Sunday night.
	   Lindros flicked a loose puck past Guy Hebert early in the first
period. He scored the Flyers' final goal with a slap shot from the
right circle 50 seconds into the third.
	   John LeClair, seeking his fourth straight 50-goal season, scored
his first with 6{ minutes left in the first period as the first
line of Lindros, LeClair and rookie Mike Maneluk accounted for
seven of the Flyers' 11 points.
	   New Flyers goaltender John Vanbiesbrouck had a solid home debut,
giving up only Paul Kariya's goal in the first period en route to a
21-save performance.
 &UR; Senators 4, Coyotes 1 &QC; 
	   In Phoenix, Bruce Gardiner had a goal and an assist as Ottawa
beat Phoenix to open the season with consecutive wins for the first
time in franchise history.
	   Andreas Dackell scored for the second time in as many nights and
Radek Bonk and Magnus Arvedson added goals for the Senators, who
are unbeaten in their last eight road games dating back to last
season.
	   Jeremy Roenick scored for the Coyotes (0-1-0), who lost a home
opener for the first time since moving from Winnipeg before the
1996-97 season.
	   The Senators, who beat Colorado 4-3 on Saturday, have posted a
2-1-4 mark in opening games since joining the NHL in 1992-93.
</TEXT>
