<HEADLINE>
Bear kills woman picking berries in Siberia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A brown bear attacked two women picking berries in
Siberia, killing one of them and injuring the other, the ITAR-Tass
news agency said Monday.
	   The two women from the Ovgort settlement went to the tundra to
pick blueberries and cranberries when they were attacked near some
homes, the news agency said. One died instantly; the other was
rushed to a hospital by neighbors who came to her aid.
	   Local hunters say the bear may have been roused from an early
hibernation.
