Foreign oil companies donate money to areas hit by forest fires
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ American oil companies donated dlrs 50,000 to
communities in the Russian Far East seriously damaged by forest
fires, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported Monday.
	   The money from Exxon Neftegaz Ltd., Mobil and Texaco will be
used to help rebuild communications and power lines on Sakhalin
