<SLUG> BC-Kyrgyzstan-Afghanistan </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Kyrgyz officials seize weapons intended for Afghanistan
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Customs officials in Kyrgyzstan found weapons and
explosives hidden among humanitarian aid on an Iranian train, and
believe they were going to be smuggled into Afghanistan, a news
agency said Monday.
	   Customs officials inspected the 16-car Iranian train in the
southern Kyrgyz city of Osh, ITAR-Tass said. A large number of
weapons and explosives was found hidden in the humanitarian aid, it
said.
	   Documents found on the train indicate the shipment was to be
loaded onto trucks and taken into Afghanistan, ITAR-Tass said,
quoting the deputy chairman of the State Customs Inspectorate,
Nadyrbek Turganbayev. He refused to give any more details.
	   Kyrgyzstan and other former Soviet republics in Central Asia
fear an influx of refugees and weapons from Afghanistan, and
possibly a spill over of fighting that has wracked the country.
