<HEADLINE>
Needy families given rice aid in drought-affected province
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HANOI, Vietnam (AP) _ The Vietnamese Red Cross has provided an
additional 217 tons of rice for 10,850 of the neediest victims from
a recent drought in Quang Binh province.
	   The provincial Red Cross said Monday that each person was given
20 kilograms (44 pounds) of rice, with a maximum of 60 kilograms
(132 pounds) for one family. Another 93 tons had been donated
earlier.
	   The province, one of Vietnam's poorest, suffered from its worst
drought in half a century until rains finally came in mid-August.
