<SLUG> BC-Vietnam-Food Poisoning </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Dozens struck with food poisoning after thank-you meal
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HANOI, Vietnam (AP) _ A thank-you meal for villagers who helped
a man put a roof on his house left 76 of them sick with food
poisoning, a district hospital said Monday.
	   Six of the villagers had to be hospitalized overnight in Kien
Xuuong district in the northern province of Thai Binh.
	   Doctors said water used to cook the meal had been taken from the
nearby river, which was contaminated with the cholera virus.
	   The Health Ministry was quoted last week as saying 292 people
died among 6,103 food-poisoning cases in 1997.
	   The total of 3,517 cases and 156 fatalities in the first six
months this year is ahead of that pace. Excessive use of
insecticide is being blamed.
</TEXT>
