<HEADLINE>
Russian parliamentary speaker to visit China, maybe defense
</HEADLINE>
minister &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ The speaker of the Russian parliament will visit
China from Oct. 25-30, the parliament's press office said Monday.
	   Gennady Seleznyov is expected to meet with Chinese President
Jiang Zemin, Prime Minister Zhu Rongji and his counterpart, Li
Peng, chairman of the standing committee of the All-China Assembly
of People's Representatives.
	   Seleznyov will also address the Chinese legislature, said Viktor
Cheryomukhin, head of the press office of the State Duma, the lower
house of the Russian parliament.
	   Meanwhile, the Defense Ministry said that Russian Defense
Minister Igor Sergeyev may also visit China later this month.
	   The ITAR-Tass news agency said Sergeyev's trip would take place
Oct. 21-24, and that he was also expected to meet with Jiang, Zhu
Rongji and his Chinese counterpart, Chi Haotian.
	   (ls) 	   
