<SLUG> BC-Lesotho </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Two more dead from Lesotho rally violence
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MASERU, Lesotho (AP) _ Two people died at a hospital here to
raise the death toll to three from violence at a ruling-party
rally, officials said Monday.
	   The victims had been beaten Sunday by supporters of the ruling
Lesotho Congress for Democracy after a shot was fired by an
unidentified person.
	   The crowd believed the victims were opposition party supporters
who had infiltrated the rally and allegedly were trying to plant a
bomb, the South African Press Association reported.
	   Dr. Thabo McPherson, superintendent at Queen Elizabeth II
Hospital, said the two people died on Sunday night from severe head
injuries, SAPA reported.
	   A fourth person was in critical condition, also with serious
head injuries. Another person died at the scene.
	   The violence has raised tensions in the mountain kingdom of 2
million people within South Africa's borders.
	   After an army revolt and crippling strikes, South Africa and
nearby Botswana last month sent about 1,000 troops into the country
to restore calm, but scores were killed and the downtown destroyed
by looters.
	   (djw)	   
</TEXT>
