<HEADLINE>
Russian town sealed off after dysentery outbreak
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A town in southern Russia has been sealed off
after 70 residents were diagnosed with dysentery over the weekend,
a news agency reported Monday.
	   Health care workers in Verkhny Balyklei, about 900 kilometers
(550 miles) southeast of Moscow, are still trying to figure out the
cause of the outbreak, the ITAR-Tass news agency said.
	   Dysentery is an intestinal infection, whose symptoms include
abdominal pain and severe diarrhea. Severe cases can prove fatal,
particularly in unhealthy people, children or the elderly.
