Germany closes embassy in Belgrade
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BONN, Germany (AP) _ Germany on Monday closed its embassy in the
Yugoslav capital, Belgrade, and its ambassador left the country
with the remaining embassy staff, the Foreign Ministry announced.
	   The ministry urged Germans living in the Yugolsav republics of
Serbia and Montenegro to leave the country.
	   Germany's Cabinet decides Monday whether to support threatened
NATO air strikes aimed at stopping bloodshed in the Serbian
province of Kosovo.
