<HEADLINE>
Dollar higher; gold down
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar was higher against most other
major currencies in European trading Monday morning. Gold prices
fell.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Friday:
	   _1.6484 German marks, up from 1.6386
	   _118.15 Japanese yen, up from 117.90
	   _1.3355 Swiss francs, up from 1.3290
	   _5.5264 French francs, up from 5.4945
	   _1.8588 Dutch guilders, up from 1.8485
	   _1,631.90 Italian lire, up from 1,622.22
	   _1.5320 Canadian dollars, down from 1.5470
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6888, down from dlrs
1.7077.
	   Gold dealers in London fixed a recommended price of dlrs 296.65
bid per troy ounce at midmorning, down from dlrs 298.70 on Friday.
	   In Zurich the bid price was dlrs 296.40, down from dlrs 298.25.
	   Gold fell 20 cents in Hong Kong to dlrs 296.35.
	   Silver opened in London at dlrs 4.85 bid per troy ounce, down
from dlrs 4.86.
	   (mj)
