<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Mine Death </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukrainian miner killed in rock collapse
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ Pieces of coal fell in a deep mine shaft in
eastern Ukraine on Monday, killing a miner, officials said.
	   The accident occurred at the depth of 540 meters (1,782 feet) at
the Olkhovatska mine in the coal-rich Donetsk region, the Emergency
Situations Ministry reported.
	   At least 302 people have died in coal mine accidents in Ukraine
so far this year, about 100 more than the same period last year,
according to government statistics.
	   Ukraine's cash-strapped mines lack the funds needed to improve
safety conditions and modernize equipment, which has led to a
steady increase in work-related fatalities in recent years.
	   The worst single accident this year was in April, when a methane
gas blast killed 63 workers at a mine in Donetsk.
	   (vl/sms/ls) 	   
