<SLUG> BC-Russia-Explosion </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Explosion in southern Russian kills boy
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ An explosive device in the southern Russian town
of Petrov Val killed an 8-year-old boy and seriously injured
another, the ITAR-Tass news agency said Monday.
	   The device exploded when the two boys were playing with a green
object they had found in a ravine, said a third boy who left before
the blast took place.
	   Police in the nearby city of Volgograd, 900 kilometers (550
miles) southeast of Moscow, were called in to investigate.
	   ITAR-Tass gave no other details.
	   (ls)	   
</TEXT>
