<HEADLINE>
Yeltsin cuts short trip to Central Asia
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with Yeltsin cutting short trip and returning to
Moscow. &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos planned &QL; 
 &UR; By TIMOFEI ZHUKOV
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   TASHKENT, Uzbekistan (AP) _ Russian President Boris Yeltsin, who
is suffering from a cold, will cut short his trip to Central Asia
and return to Moscow on Monday, one day ahead of schedule, Russian
news agencies said.
	   No reason was given for the change in plans.
