<HEADLINE>
U.S. soldier in Germany shot at by unknown assailant
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) _ A U.S. soldier was shot and wounded
slightly late Sunday while on guard duty outside a barracks at a
military airfield in Erlensee east of Frankfurt, the U.S. Army said
Monday.
	   The female soldier, who was not identified, was apparently shot
by an assailant in a nearby field. No arrests have been made.
German and American authorities were cooperating on an
investigation.
	   The soldier was taken to hospital for treatment after a bullet
apparently hit her bullet-proof vest then grazed her neck.
	   The Army's public affairs division could not immediately be
reached for further comment.
