<SLUG> BC-Philippines-Tornado </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Tornado destroys houses in two southern Philippine villages
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ZAMBOANGA Philippines (AP) _ A tornado tore through two coastal
villages in the southern Philippines, injuring at least a dozen
people and destroying several grass huts, officials said Monday.
	   The tornado struck late Friday the villages in Lamitan town in
the island province of Basilan, which has been swamped by monsoon
rains for a week, Gov. Wahab Akbar said.
	   At least 20 huts were destroyed in the villages of Bato and
Banas, leaving about 100 people homeless, Akbar said.
	   Pounding rains also have hit the nearby province of Zamboanga
for days, destroying wide swaths of agricultural land and
fishponds, officials said.
	   At least three people have died in floods in Zamboanga, they
said.
	   Basilan and Zamboanga are located in the southern region of
Mindanao, about 850 kilometers (527 miles) south of Manila. 	   
</TEXT>
