<HEADLINE>
F.A. charges Hartson with misconduct for kicking teammate
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ West Ham striker John Hartson was charged Monday
with misconduct by the Football Association for kicking teammate
Eyal Berkovic in the head in a training ground incident.
	   The Welsh international was fined 10,000 pounds (dlrs 17,000) by
West Ham last week, with Hammers manager Harry Redknapp saying he
hoped that was the end of the incident.
	   But after a review of the video which shows Hartson kicking a
prone Berkovic in the face, the F.A. decided to charge him with
misconduct.
	   Hartson has 14 days to respond to the charge.
	   The incident sparked outrage last week when a series of graphic
photographs published in the Mirror showed Hartson kicking Berkovic
the face during the leadup to West Ham's Sept. 28 match against
Southampton.
	   Berkovic, an Israel international, was quoted as saying he was
in agony and was unable to eat for two days after the incident.
	   He also said he was considering leaving West Ham because he
could not ``forgive and forget'' what Hartson had done.
	   ``If my head was a ball it would have been (kicked into) the top
corner of the net,'' Berkovic said.
