<HEADLINE>
Floods kill 14 in Iran
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TEHRAN, Iran (AP) _ Floods unleashed by heavy rains have killed
14 people in northern Iran, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported Monday.
	   The floods, which occurred over the past few days in northern
Gilan Province, also killed 500 livestock and damaged farms, roads,
bridges and houses, it said.
	   The damage was estimated at 50 billion rials (dlrs 17 million).
