<HEADLINE>
Britain closing embassy in Yugoslavia
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With Yugoslavia-Kosovo &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Britain will close its embassy in Belgrade on
Monday afternoon, the Foreign Office said as preparations
heightened for possible NATO airstrikes against Serb forces in the
Yugoslav province of Kosovo.
	   British Ambassador Brian Donnelly and his remaining staff would
leave Yugoslavia by road for Hungary as a ``precautionary
measure,'' the Foreign Office said in an announcement made on the
British Broadcasting Corp. World Service.
	   The announcement was aimed at British nationals remaining in
Yugoslavia.
	   (mj)
