<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Nobel-Medicine-Nitric Oxide, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
What nitric oxide does
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: DELETES word 'odorless' in lede &QL; 
 &UR; With BC-Nobel-Medicine &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) _ Nitric oxide, a colorless gas, is a
common pollutant, formed by combustion of nitrogen such as in
automobile exhaust pipes.
	   The gas has a wide range of effects and potential applications,
according to the Karolinska Institute, which awarded the Nobel
Medicine Prize to three American researchers for their discoveries
about the gas.
	   Among its effects and applications, according to the prize
citation:
	   _ It acts as a weapon against infections, as a regulator of
blood pressure and as a gatekeeper of blood flow to different
organs. It controls blood pressure and its distribution, and also
prevents the formation of thrombi.
	   _ White blood cells use nitric oxide to not only to kill
infectious agents such as bacteria, fungi and parasites, but also
to defend the host against tumors. Scientists are currently testing
whether nitric oxide cane be used to stop the growth of tumors.
	   _ Nitric oxide can initiate erection of the penis by dilating
the blood vessels to the erectile bodies.
	   _ Nitric oxide is important for the olfactory sense and the
capacity to recognize different scents.
	   (mhh-jh)
</TEXT>
