<HEADLINE>
U.S. first lady arrives in Prague
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PRAGUE, Czech Republic (AP) _ U.S. first lady Hillary Rodham
Clinton arrived in Prague Monday, in what is the second leg of her
four-day trip to promote women's rights and civil society in
Eastern Europe.
	   Braving cold rain as she walked on a red carpet towards her
limousine, Mrs. Clinton briefly waved at the press and left the
airport.
	   Mrs.Clinton is scheduled to deliver a keynote speech on Tuesday
at the Forum 2000 conference in Prague before returning to
Washington on the same day.
	   The prestigious gathering of over 50 thinkers, political and
religious activists includes former U.S. Secretary of State Henry
Kissinger, former Polish premier Hana Suchocka and the chief rabbi
of Israel, Meir Lau.
