<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Bakayoko-Everton </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Bakayoko signs 4.5 million pound deal with Everton
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LIVERPOOL, England (AP) _ Ibrahim Bakayoko became Everton
manager Walter Smith's latest acquisition Monday when the Ivory
Coast international signed a 4.5 million pound (dlrs 7.65 million)
transfer deal.
	   The 21-year-old striker signed a five-year contract to move from
Montpellier, where he earned a reputation as one of the leading
strikers in the French league over the last three years.
	   Everton is 14th in the Premier League standings with two wins
from eight matches but has not scored a goal in four home matches.
	   The signing of Bakayoko is Smith's latest bid to increase his
strike power and he could make his Premier League debut within
days.
	   Bakayoko is expected to be rushed into the Everton team for the
Merseyside derby clash against Liverpool at Goodison Park on
Saturday.
	   ``The Liverpool match could be my first game, and I can hardly
wait for it. I just want to get going and am looking forward for
the challenge,'' he said Monday.
	   (jp)
</TEXT>
