<SLUG> BC-Sports-Baseball-Japan Roundup </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Marines edge Lions 5-4 in last regular season game
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TOKYO (AP) _ Brian Warren gave up no hits after the seventh to
lead the Chiba Lotte Marines to a 5-4 win against the 1998 Pacific
League champion Seibu Lions 5-4 Monday in the league's last regular
season game.
	   Makoto Kosaka of the Marines drove in the winning run at Seibu
Dome in the top of the ninth with a sacrifice fly.
	   Warren, formerly with the Texas Rangers, was 2-1 with 0.93 ERA
this season.
	   The Lions will meet the Central League winners, Yokohama
BayStars, in the best-of-seven Japan Series starting Saturday at
Yokohama Stadium. The Marines ended up in last place in the
six-team league this season.
	   In Central League action, Kenjiro Nomura smashed a grand slam in
the second inning, as the Hiroshima Toyo Carp beat the BayStars 4-0
at Yokohama.
	   Nomura had 14 homers this season and his team ended fifth in the
six-team league.
	   At Koshien Stadium, Yutaka Wada drew a bases-loaded walk in the
first inning and drove in a run with a sacrifice fly in a two-run
third as the Hanshin Tigers beat the Chunichi Dragons 4-2.
	   The Dragons placed second and the Tigers were last.
	   The league's all scheduled regular season games were completed
Monday.
