<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Malaysia-Swaziland </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Swaziland, Malaysia want to up co-operation: Report
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) _ Swaziland and Malaysia have agreed
to increase economic co-operation between the two nations, the
national Bernama news agency reported Monday.
	   The agreement came after King Mswati from the southern African
nation, who arrived here Sunday for a six-day visit, met with
Malaysian Prime Minister Minister Mahathir Mohamad, the report
said.
	   Mahathir and Mswati attended a signing ceremony on agreements on
trade and scientific, technical and cultural co-operation, it said.
	   Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi signed on behalf of
Malaysia while Swaziland was represented by the Minister of Foreign
Affairs and Trade, Albert H.N. Shabangu.
</TEXT>
