<SLUG> BC-Bosnia-US, 1st Ld </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
American, German officials ordered out of Serb-held half of Bosnia
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with German Embassy closing office in Banja Luka,
RECASTS overline to accommodate
 &UR; With AP Photo
 &UR; By SRECKO LATAL &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   SARAJEVO, Bosnia-Herzegovina (AP) _ All American officials were
ordered out of the Serb-held half of Bosnia on Monday, ahead of
possible NATO military intervention in neighboring Yugoslavia.
	   The German Embassy closed its office in the northwestern Bosnian
Serb town of Banja Luka and advised other German organizations to
leave, an embassy official said.
	   The only British Embassy representative in the Serb-held area
will remain in Banja Luka, but may move to another office for
security reasons, another diplomat said.
