r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Ukraine-Kosovo     10-12 0221
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Kosovo </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukraine offering mediation services in Kosovo
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ Ukraine is offering to mediate in the
Kosovo conflict and has already started discussing its offer with
Yugoslavia and the United States, Foreign Minister Borys Tarasiuk
said Monday.
	   Ukraine is prepared to participate in a mission to Kosovo by the
54-nation Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe,
Tarasiuk said. Ukrainian leaders have suggested former Foreign
Minister Hennady Udovenko as a possible mediator.
	   Ukraine says it would support NATO airstrikes against Serb
forces, provided that other possibilities to resolve the conflict
prove fruitless and the U.N. Security Council approves the use of
force.
	   ``Not all the possibilities for a peaceful solution have been
exhausted'' in Kosovo, a predominantly ethnic Albanian province in
Yugoslavia, Tarasiuk said. NATO is considering airstrikes there to
end the violent Serb crackdown.
	   The foreign minister also said Ukraine was consulting with
neighboring Russia over Kosovo and was ``well aware of all the
arguments and the Russian stance'' on the issue.
	   Russia opposes possible NATO attacks on Serbia, a traditional
ally with which it shares a Slavic heritage and Orthodox Christian
religion.
	   (sms/ji) 	   
</TEXT>
