w1362 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Germany-Obit-Minetti     10-12 0200
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Germany-Obit-Minetti </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
German actor Bernhard Minetti dies at 93
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) _ Bernhard Minetti, a German actor whose
career began in the Prussian State Theater in 1930 and spanned most
of this century, died on Monday. He was 93.
	   Minetti, who had appeared increasingly frail in recent years,
died in a Berlin hospital where he was admitted two weeks ago, a
spokeswoman for the Berlin Ensemble theater said. She said the
exact cause of death was not known.
	   Minetti was one of the last great German actors of the century.
He worked with such legendary German actors as Gustaf Gruendgens
and appear in most of Germany's best-known theaters.
	   Minetti was born in 1905 in Kehl, a small German town on the
Rhine river close to the French city of Strasbourg.
	   He appeared most recently with the Berlin Ensemble, playing the
role of an actor in ``The Resistible Rise of Arturo Ui,'' a play by
Bertolt Brecht.
	   Minetti's most important roles included ``Krapp'' in Samuel
Beckett's ``Krapp's Last Tape,'' ``Faust'' in Goethe's version of
the classic, and ``Lear'' in Shakespeare's ``King Lear.''
	   Funeral plans were not immediately announced.
	    &UR; ms-dkt-gb
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
