<HEADLINE>
Arsonists burn psychiatric hospital car
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Arsonists burned a car belonging to a
state psychiatric hospital Monday, causing extensive damage to
other vehicles parked nearby but no injuries, police said.
	   A total of six cars were destroyed when fire spread after a
makeshift gas canister bomb exploded under the Dafni hospital car,
parked in the southeastern Athens suburb of Ilioupolis.
	   The attack caused an estimated 10 million drachmas (dlrs 35,000)
worth of damage, police said.
	   A previously unknown organization calling itself Anarchist
Groups of Crisis claimed responsibility for the attack in a
telephone call to a small private radio station.
	   During the past year, arsonists have targeted numerous cars with
diplomatic, government and foreign license plates. On average,
about 300 cars are firebombed in Greece every year.
	   (eb) 	   
