<HEADLINE>
Bulgaria bans investment in Serbia
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SOFIA, Bulgaria (AP) _ Bulgaria on Monday joined a European
Union ban on investment in Yugoslavia's main republic of Serbia.
	   The European Union has endorsed the punitive measure because of
Belgrade's crackdown on independence seeking Albanians in
Yugoslavia's southern province of Kosovo.
	   The ban doesn't affect Bulgarian-Serbian commercial contracts
that have been concluded before it, Bulgarian trade minister
Valentin Vasilev said.
	   He added so far Bulgarian investment in Serbia was
insignificant.
	   On Saturday, Bulgaria said it was ready to allow NATO aircraft
use its airspace for possible attacks on Yugoslavia. However, the
permit has to be finally approved by parliament if the alliance
resorts to airstrikes.
