<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Military </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Official: Ukraine's military draft hampered by massive evasion
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ The vast majority of young men are evading
the military draft this year, hampering Ukraine's efforts to
recruit soldiers, a senior military official said Monday.
	   The military can count on actually drafting only 6.7 percent, or
54,500, of those eligible for army service _ just 5,000 more than
are to be called into service this fall, said Mykola Matiukh,
Ukraine's deputy chief of staff.
	   ``There's practically no one to choose from,'' Matiukh
complained.
	   He said most potential conscripts are either evading military
service illegally or cannot be drafted because they study at
universities or have health problems.
	   Ukraine's army, like those in other former Soviet republics, has
been badly hurt by the 1991 Soviet collapse and ensuing economic
problems. The force has been reduced by nearly one-third from its
pre-independence level of 900,000 servicemen.
	   Many young Ukrainians are unwilling to spend the required 18
months in the army, fearing hazing by veteran soldiers and poor
conditions that stem from chronic under-financing of the military's
needs.
	   Matiukh told reporters that massive evasion from military
service forces the army to draft conscripts with a low educational
level and imperfect health, which badly affects the military's
fighting potential.
	   Only 0.5 percent of young people eligible for this year's draft
have higher education, while about a third of them have not
completed secondary education, he added.
	   Ukraine's army is to be reduced to 320,000 servicemen by the end
of 1998, and by 10,000 more in 1999, according to the Defense
Ministry.
	   (vl/sms/ji) 	   
</TEXT>
