u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Netherlands-Stocks     10-12 0209
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Netherlands-Stocks </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Boosted by Wall Street, Amsterdam bourse closes sharply higher
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) _ Prices on the Amsterdam Stock
Exchange closed sharply higher Monday, boosted by surging Asian
markets, a stronger dollar and a strong performance on Wall Street.
	   The Dutch market had been on the rise the entire day, but shares
were given a further boost by strong gains on Wall Street when its
trade started in the European afternoon.
	   The 27-share AEX Index finished at 899.65 points, up 48.54
points, or 5.7 percent.
	   The dollar was fetching 1.85 guilders at 1435 GMT, up from late
Friday's 1.84 guilders.
	   Financial stocks were the biggest risers after the sharp losses
seen in recent weeks. Shares of leading Dutch bank ABN Amro closed
up 9.3 percent Monday, and the ING financial services group surged
12 percent.
	   The main loser Monday was Dutch software company Baan, which
issued a profit warning before the start of trade. The company said
it expects third-quarter losses of between 13 cents and 16 cents a
share on the back of the global economic problems.
	   Its shares plummeted to close down 29 percent after falling as
far as 42 percent earlier in the day.
	   (dj/bk)
</TEXT>
