<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-Singapore Open,0200 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Courier advances through first round of Singapore Open
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SINGAPORE (AP) _ Former world No. 1 Jim Courier took advantage
of his wild card status to advance through the opening round of the
Singapore Open tennis tournament on Monday.
	   Courier, an American who won four Grand Slam titles but is
currently ranked 102 in the world, defeated Canada's Daniel Nestor
6-3, 6-2 in the first day's play at the dlrs 700,000 ATP Tour
tournament.
	   Despite recent problems with a lingering arm injury and several
poor performances, Courier made short work of Nestor.
	   Australian teenager Lleyton Hewitt produced the other notable
preliminary round performance, beating France's Lionel Roux 6-2,
7-6(8).
	   Hewitt, 17, is the youngest player currently in the top 200 ATP
tour singles players, ranked 139.
	   Also advancing past the first round on Monday was the
Netherlands' Sjeng Schalken, New Zealand's Brett Steven, and
Romania's Andrei Pavel.
	   Preliminary round singles action in the 32-player tournament
continues Tuesday and Wednesday, with Marcelo Rios of Chile, Goran
Ivanisevic of Croatia and American Michael Chang taking to the
court.
</TEXT>
