<HEADLINE>
Brother of Yugoslav president country's new ambassador to Moscow
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) _ Seeking to further strengthen ties
with a traditional ally, Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic
dispatched his brother to Moscow as the country's new ambassador to
Russia, media here reported Monday.
	   Before departing for Russian capital, Borislav Milosevic met
Monday Yugoslav defense minister Pavle Bulatovic, independent Beta
news agency carried.
	   Bulatovic wished Milosevic success at his new post and stressed
the necessity to improve further on Russian-Yugoslav relations,
particularly in matters of defense.
