<TEXT>
	   The source, speaking on condition of anonymity, said Holbrooke
wanted to brief NATO ambassadors on the results of his talks with
Milosevic aimed at convincing him to accept U.N. demands for ending
the crackdown in Kosovo.
	   Ambassadors from the 16 NATO members were meeting Monday at
