tried to broker a deal that would avoid NATO intervention, was
prepared to provide planes and consider participating in the
monitoring force.
	   Ambassadors from the 16 NATO members were meeting Monday at
headquarters in Brussels, Belgium to consider whether to approve an
activation order, the last military step before airstrikes can be
launched.
	   A U.S. source, speaking condition of anonymity, indicated that
Holbrooke had made enough progress that he needed to update NATO
personally.
	   A NATO official who spoke on condition of anonymity said an
activation order would show NATO's resolve to end the violence in
Kosovo, where hundreds of people have been killed and an estimated
