r w &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-WeatherSummary     10-12 1070
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,1087 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Fair to partly cloudy skies were observed across the local area
this morning as early morning showers and thunderstorms died over
water well before sunrise, leaving isolated showers across the
local waters. However, numerous showers and thunderstorms
associated with a tropical wave were beginning to spread into large
portions of the eastern Caribbean and will threaten our area by
Tuesday morning.
	   An upper-level low pressure system located over the Mona Passage
is expected to maintain very unstable atmospheric conditions
locally for the next few days, producing a good chance for
afternoon showers and thunderstorms across the mountains and
interior of Puerto Rico. Partly cloudy skies across the local
islands through noon time today will give way to increasing clouds
and the development of scattered showers and thunderstorms across
interior and western Puerto Rico. Widely scattered to scattered
showers and a few thunderstorms are expected to affect the
remainder of the local area, including the Virgin Islands and the
local coastal waters. A few of these showers and thunderstorms will
produce very heavy rainfall and dangerous lightning. Urban and
stream flooding should be expected across the interior of Puerto
Rico this afternoon.
	   A very active tropical wave moving into the Lesser Antilles this
morning is expected to bring widespread showers and thunderstorms
to the Virgin Islands beginning after midnight tonight and reaching
eastern Puerto Rico around sunrise Tuesday morning. Tuesday through
much of Tuesday night could prove to be a very rainy period for the
local islands as the tropical wave moves westward through the
region and very heavy rainfall will be possible across the entire
area.
 &UR; San Juan and north sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Partly cloudy morning. Increasing clouds afternoon
with a 40 percent chance of showers. Isolated thunderstorms. High
around 90. Wind northeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy. A 30 percent chance of showers. Low
near 75. Wind east 5 to 10 mph.
	   Tuesday ... Partly cloudy morning. Increasing clouds afternoon
with a 40 percent chance of showers. Isolated thunderstorms. High
85 to 90. Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 mph.
 &UR; East sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
High 85 to 90. Wind northeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy. A 30 percent chance of showers.
Isolated coastal thunderstorms. Low 70 to near 80. Wind east 5 to
10 mph.
	   Tuesday ... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Isolated thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east to southeast.
 &UR; Ponce and south sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Variably cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers.
Possible thunderstorms inland and west. High 90 to 95. Wind
northeast 10 to 15 mph except southeast along the coast.
	   Tonight ... Variable cloudiness. A 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 70 to 75. Wind light northeast.
	   Tuesday ... Partly cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers.
Possible afternoon thunderstorms inland. High near 90 to 95. Wind
southeast 10 to 15 mph.
 &UR; Mayaguez and west sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Sunny morning. Variably cloudy afternoon with a 50
percent chance of showers and thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind
northeast 10 to 15 mph except variable along the coast.
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy. Low 65 to 75. Wind light east.
	   Tuesday ... Partly sunny morning. Becoming mostly cloudy
afternoon with a 50 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms.
High 85 to 90. Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 mph.
 &UR; Interior sections of Puerto Rico
	   Today ... Partly sunny morning. Increasing cloudiness afternoon
with a 40 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms. High from 75
to 80 mountains to 85 to 90 low elevations. Wind northeast 10 to 15
mph.
	   Tonight ... Variable cloudiness. A 20 percent chance of showers.
Low 65 to 70 mountains to 70 to 75 low valleys. Wind east 5 to 10
mph.
	   Tuesday ... Partly cloudy morning. Increasing cloudiness
afternoon. A 50 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms in the
afternoon. High 75 to near 80 mountains to 80 to near 90 low
elevations. Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 mph.
 &UR; St. Thomas, St. John and St. Croix
	   This afternoon ... Partly sunny with a 30 percent chance of
showers. Chance for thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east to
northeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight ... Becoming variably cloudy. A 50 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms, mainly after midnight. Low 75 to 80.
Wind east to northeast 5 mph except gusty near thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday ... Becoming mostly cloudy with a 60 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms. High 80 to 90. Wind east to southeast
near 15 mph.
 &UR; Puerto Rico and U.S. Virgin Islands waters
	   Synopsis ... High pressure over the central Atlantic northeast
of the local region will shift gradually northeast through Tuesday
night to maintain moderate trade winds across the local waters.
Tropical wave with numerous showers and thunderstorms moving west
near 15 kt will reach the Windward Islands early this afternoon,
the Leeward Islands this evening, the U.S. Virgin Islands Tuesday
morning and Puerto Rico by Tuesday afternoon.
 &UR; Atlantic waters
	   This afternoon ... Wind east 10 to 15 kt. Seas 4 to 6 ft in
northeast swells. Widely scattered showers. Wind and seas higher
near isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight ... Wind east to northeast 10 to 15 kt. Seas 4 to 6 ft
in northeast swells. Scattered showers. Widely scattered
thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday ... Wind becoming east to seast near 15 kt. Seas 4 to 5
ft in northeast swells. Scattered showers and thunderstorms.
 &UR; Caribbean waters
	   Small craft exercise caution Anegada Passage.
	   This afternoon ... Wind east near 15 kt. Seas 4 to 5 ft, except
seas to 7 ft Anegada Passage in northeast swells. Widely scattered
showers. Wind and seas higher near isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight ... Wind east to northeast 10 to 15 kt. Seas 3 to 5 ft,
except seas to 6 ft Anegada Passage in northeast swells. Scattered
showers and thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday ... Wind becoming east to seast 15 kt. Seas 4 to 5 ft.
Scattered to numerous showers. Widely scattered thunderstorms. 	   
</TEXT>
