<SLUG> BC-Ireland-Handbag Thief </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Handbag thief gets sentencing break, but still must serve three
</HEADLINE>
years &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   DUBLIN, Ireland (AP) _ An Irish woman ordered imprisoned for
nine years for stealing a handbag received a sentence reduction
Monday _ but still must serve six years.
	   Sabrina Walsh, 20, was originally sentenced in Dublin's Circuit
Court in June after stealing a handbag containing 10,000 Irish
pounds (dlrs 7,000) and jewellery from an English tourist in a
cafe.
	   Walsh's lawyer, Fergal Foley, argued for a reduction in the
sentence, saying his client had not been aware of the contents of
the bag when she stole it.
	   The Irish Court of Criminal Appeal agreed to lower the sentence
to six years, but Judge Hugh O'Flaherty warned that
handbag-snatching was ``like a cancer on society'' and had to be
stamped out.
	   He said people involved in stealing handbags ``will get
exemplary sentences from now on.''
