<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Icon Smuggling </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ukrainian court sentences two women for icon smuggling
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ A Ukrainian court sentenced two women to
prison for trying to smuggle valuable icons abroad, a news agency
reported Monday.
	   The court in the city of Evpatoria on the Crimean Peninsula gave
each of the two unidentified women three years in prison after they
acknowledged their attempt to smuggle 20 icons dating back to the
early 19th century, Interfax reported.
	   The women were arrested last October in Evpatoria, located on
Crimea's Black Sea coast. On the same day, local customs officers
discovered the icons in a garbage container on a passenger ship
that was about to leave for Turkey.
	   Investigators found out that the women had brought the icons on
board under their clothes, and planned to sell them abroad.
	   The confiscated icons were valued at dlrs 6,000, Interfax said.
