<HEADLINE>
Chang captures Heineken Open
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES throughout with details, size of prize &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   SHANGHAI, China (AP) _ Continuing his dominance in Asia,
second-seeded Michael Chang captured the rain-delayed dlrs 315,000
Heineken Open Monday by defeating top-seeded Goran Ivanisevic 4-6,
6-1, 6-2.
	   The final had been pushed back a day by heavy rain.
	   It was Chang's second title of the year, and his 12th in Asia.
Chang, an American of Chinese descent, won five titles last year
and finished the season ranked third in the world. But his ranking
has fallen to 33rd this season after suffering a series of
injuries.
	   Ivanisevic failed in his bid to win his second title of the
year, falling to 4-6 lifetime to Chang. The 27-year-old left-hander
has now lost three finals since winning at his hometown of Split,
Croatia, in February. He was also runner-up at Wimbledon in July.
	   Chang earned dlrs 45,000.
