<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Lithuania-Killers </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Report: organized killers nabbed in Lithuania
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   VILNIUS, Lithuania (AP) _ Lithuanian police have broken up a
ring of professional killers, believed to be responsible for more
than a dozen murders, the Lietuvos Rytas daily reported.
	   The 30-member gang, mostly ex-convicts also included at least
one established businessman and an opera singer, the newspaper said
at the weekend. About 15 of the gang members were arrested earlier
this month. Police were hunting the others, the report said.
	   The gang reportedly specialized in murder, but also carried out
several armed robberies, bombings and kidnappings, Lietuvos Rytas
said.
	   Among the alleged victims were well-known businessmen, several
currency traders and a taxi driver. In all, the gang is believed to
have been involved in 13 murders and six attempted murders from
1992 to 1998.
	   During a recent raid, police seized a large stockpile of
explosives, sub-machine guns and equipment used by gang members to
disguise themselves, the report said.
	   Lithuania experienced a sharp rise in crime after it broke from
the Soviet Union in 1991. Local police say that the murders are
often gang-related.
	   (mt/mhh)	   
</TEXT>
