<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-World Bank </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
World Bank to grant dlrs 200 million loan to Ukrainian capital
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ The World Bank will grant Kiev a dlrs 200
million loan to modernize the city's electricity and heating
systems, the mayor said Monday.
	   The loan agreement will be signed in Washington on Wednesday,
said Mayor Oleksandr Omelchenko. He is to lead a city delegation to
the United States on Tuesday.
	   The 20-year loan will be used to finance most of a dlrs 249.4
million electricity and heating system renovation project, with the
rest of the funds supplied by the Kyivenergo energy company, he
said.
	   Omelchenko said Kiev's electricity system can only provide for
86 percent of the city's needs at peak hours, while most of Kiev's
heating utilities are more than 50 years old, the Interfax news
agency reported.
	   Ukraine has received more than dlrs 1 billion for various
projects from the World Bank since it became a member in 1992.
	   Omelchenko also said that his delegation, which will stay in the
United States until Sunday, would be bringing 400 projects that
concern all aspects of the city's life and could be of interest to
potential investors.
	   (sms/ji)
</TEXT>
