<SLUG> BC-Canada-Emergency Landing,0150 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Smoky cockpit forces plane landing
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   THUNDER BAY, Ontario (AP) _ An Air Canada Airbus 320 passenger
jet was forced to make an emergency landing Sunday night after
pilots detected smoke in the cockpit.
	   ``There was a visible smoke haze in the cockpit and a smell of
smoke, so they decided to make an emergency landing,'' said Air
Canada spokesman John Hamilton.
	   The flight from Toronto to Winnipeg, Manitoba, was carrying 125
passengers. Hamilton said the landing in Thunder Bay went smoothly.
	   ``For all intents and purposes it was a normal landing. The
passengers were extremely calm _ there wasn't any nervousness or
fear on board,'' he said, adding he wasn't aware of any previous
problems with the jet.
	   The passengers flew from Thunder Bay to Winnipeg on another
plane.
	   The jet will be checked to determine the source of the smoke.
</TEXT>
