<HEADLINE>
Some 1,400 Egyptian students hospitalized after eating tainted
</HEADLINE>
biscuits &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) _ Some 1,400 children have been hospitalized
after eating tainted school biscuits, a police official said
Monday.
	   The 1,376 children were rushed to hospitals Sunday and treated
for food poisoning after eating the biscuits in various primary,
middle and secondary schools in Darin village, in the Nile delta
province of Mansoura, the official said, speaking on customary
condition of anonymity.
	   The village is 120 kilometers northeast of Cairo.
	   Most of the students were discharged from the hospitals, but
five still remain in intensive care units, the official said.
	   Maj. Gen. Fakreddin Khaled, the governor of Mansoura, ordered
police to detain the distributor of the biscuits pending an
investigation into the poisonings, the official said.
