<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo, UPDATE </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
US defense chief sees resolution of issue soon
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KUWAIT (AP) _ U.S. Defense Secretary William Cohen said Monday
he expects a resolution over U.N. demands in Kosovo within a few
days ``one way or the other.''
	   Cohen, who is visiting U.S. troops here, said the NATO allies
were moving closer to making a decision on authorizing the use of
force to force compliance with U.N. demands for peace in the
Serbian province.
	   ``I think you will see some resolution of the issue one way or
the other over the next several days,'' Cohen told reporters.
	   Cohen told some 1,000 U.S. Army troops conducting exercises in
Kuwait that he hoped that military action was not going to be
necessary.
	   ``We are hoping not to have to deploy any American troops into
Kosovo,'' he said, addressing them from a camouflaged tent.
</TEXT>
