<SLUG> BC-Puerto Rico-Weather-Urban and Small Stream Flood </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Advisory,0236
</HEADLINE>

BULLETIN-IMMEDIATE BROADCAST REQUESTED
URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY
NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN JUAN PR
303 PM AST MON OCT 12 1998

...THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE IN SAN JUAN PR HAS ISSUED AN URBAN
   AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY EFFECTIVE UNTIL 600 PM FOR
   SOUTHWEST AND WEST INTERIOR OF PUERTO...THIS INCLUDES THE
   MUNICIPALITIES OF ADJUNTAS...YAUCO...SABANA GRANDE...MARICAO AND
   SAN GERMAN...

...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WITH HEAVY RAINFALL WERE OCCURRING
   ACROSS THE WEST-INTERIOR AND SOUTHWEST SECTIONS OF PUERTO RICO.


AN UPPER LEVEL LOW NEAR HISPANIOLA COMBINED WITH AFTERNOON HEATING
WERE PRODUCING THUNDERSTORMS WITH VERY HEAVY RAIN IN SOUTHWEST PUERTO
RICO AROUND 240 PM. THESE THUNDERSTORMS WERE NEARLY STATIONARY.

TERRAINS ACROSS THE ADVISORY AREA ARE SATURATED. ADDITIONAL RAINFALL
WILL WORSEN CONDITIONS ACROSS THESE AREAS. DUE TO LACK OF TREES
AND VEGETATION ACROSS THESE AREAS RUNOFF WILL BE QUICK THUS MAKING
MUDSLIDES PROBABLE.

MOTORISTS AND PEDESTRIANS IN OR PASSING THROUGH THE AREA THIS
AFTERNOON SHOULD AVOID CROSSING FLOODED ROADS...AND ALLOW EXTRA
TIME TO REACH THEIR DESTINATIONS.  REMEMBER...CARS CAN EASILY STALL
IN THE WATER AND BE CARRIED AWAY IN ANY CURRENT.  PEDESTRIANS ARE
ALSO ADVISED TO STAY AWAY FROM RISING CREEKS.
 &HT;    
