<HEADLINE>
Strawberry remains hospitalized
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NEW YORK (AP) _ New York Yankees slugger Darryl Strawberry will
have to watch Game 6 of the American League Championship from his
hospital room as he recovers from colon cancer surgery.
	   ``His spirits are good, he's gaining strength, he has no fever,
and his blood counts are normal,'' a statement from
Columbia-Presbyterian Medical Center said Monday. ``He is not yet
able to eat normally and therefore will remain in the hospital for
several more days.''
	   The hospital declined further comment.
	   A 16-inch portion of the outfielder's large intestine was
removed during a three-hour operation Oct. 3 to get rid of a 2
1/2-inch (6.35-cm) cancerous tumor that nearly obstructed his
intestine.
	   The Yankees, leading the best-of-7 series 3-2, play the
Cleveland Indians in Game 6 of the American League Championship
Series Tuesday night. His teammates have stitched Strawberry's No.
39 on the back of their baseball caps.
