<SLUG> BC-Congo,0105 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Congolese rebels say they capture strategic eastern air base
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 
 &UR; By HRVOJE HRANJSKI &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   KALIMA, Congo (AP) _ Congolese rebels and their Rwandan allies
on Monday said they captured Kindu, a strategic government-held air
base in the eastern part of the country.
	   After eight days of fighting, a rebel commander said 9,000 rebel
fighters entered the town and its air base, 80 kilometers (50
miles) southwest of Kalima, at around 7 p.m. (1700 GMT).
	   ``The whole town and the airport are in our hands,'' Arthur
Mulunda, a rebel battalion commander, said.
