w1981 &Cx1f; wstm-
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Congo 2ndAdd   10-12 0122
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Congo, 2nd Add,0121 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KALIMA, Congo: Kabila's home.
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ``This is a big victory for us,'' Mulunda said. ``Kabila wanted
to use Kindu for a big counter-offensive. He cannot do anything
now,'' he said. ``Mbuji-Mayi is next.''
	   The rebels _ ethnic Tutsis, disenchanted members of Kabila's
army and opposition politicians _ have been reinforced with troops
and weapons from neighboring Rwanda.
	   Kabila has so far refused to negotiate with the rebels, accusing
them of being the puppets of Rwanda and neighboring Uganda.
	   Both countries say they have legitimate security interests in
eastern Congo and accuse Kabila of failing to rid the border area
of Rwandan and Ugandan rebels.
	    &UR; MORE
</TEXT>
