w2251 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Australia-ChildSexOff     10-12 0368
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Australia-Child Sex Offender </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Accused pedophile enticed boys with gifts, then discarded them in
</HEADLINE>
teen years, court told &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) _ Accused child molester Phillip Harold
Bell seduced young boys with gifts, used them for sex and discarded
them when they became too old for his pleasure, a Sydney court was
told Tuesday.
	   Bell, 62, is on trial charged with 38 sexual offenses involving
five boys in their early teens committed in Sydney during the mid
1980s.
	   Bell pleaded innocent Monday to all the charges.
	   Bell was arrested last December in South Africa after fleeing
Australia. An international search lasting longer than a year found
him running a surfing school at Jeffrey's Bay, on South Africa's
southern coast.
	   Bell was extradited back to Australia after spending nearly five
months in jail near Port Elizabeth.
	   In the District Court in Sydney, prosecutor Mark Tedeschi said
Bell preyed on vulnerable youths for his own sexual gratification,
using a ``monotonously similar,'' method in each case.
	   Bell allegedly enticed the boys with offers of cash for odd
jobs, showered them with gifts and privileges in return for an
escalating sexual relationship, Tedeschi said.
	   Prosecutors allege the crimes took place at breachfront and
rural properties owned by Bell and on boats in Sydney Harbor.
	   Bell set up his farm to attract young boys with offers of horse
riding, motorbikes, beach buggies, a pool table and gave presents,
including wetsuits, surfboards, clothing, motorbikes and trips, the
court was told.
	   ``This accused set up an environment at his various houses which
was a paradise for a teenage boy, except there was a heavy price to
be paid and that was to give in to his sexual demands,'' Tedeschi
said.
	   Tedeschi said Bell would keep the boys under his control by
threatening to report them to the police if they did not give in to
his sexual demands but eventually lost interest in them as they
matured.
	   ``Mr. Bell would lose interest in a boy around 16, 17 or 18 - it
was about the time the boy was achieving a degree of emotional
independence so he could see the nature of Bell's relationship with
him,'' he said.
</TEXT>
