r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-China-Trade     10-12 0159
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-China-Trade </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
China's exports slide in September
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ China's exports continued to slide in September,
falling 6.7 percent from the same month last year to dlrs 15.48
billion, the official Xinhua News Agency reported Tuesday.
	   Imports in September rose just 0.6 percent to dlrs 11.54
billion, Xinhua said. Total foreign trade dropped 3.7 percent to
dlrs 27.02 billion, the report said.
	   Exports from July to September slid 2.2 percent from the
year-earlier period, while imports in the third quarter remained
unchanged from the same quarter last year, Xinhua said.
	   Overall, China's exports in the first nine months of the year
rose 3.9 percent to dlrs 134.13 billion, while imports inched up
0.4 percent to dlrs 98.82 billion.
	   Weak demand from neighboring Asian countries and declines by
regional currencies have depressed China's export growth this year.
China's exports grew 21 percent during all of 1997.
</TEXT>
